[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     787[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Helpers for `Decimal` conversion, hashing for log safety, ID generation, and the in-memory mocks for upstream systems.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     788[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     789[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     790[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def _to_decimal(value):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     791[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     792[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Convert nested Python floats to Decimal so DynamoDB
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     793[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     accepts the payload. DynamoDB rejects float; coordination
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     794[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     state is full of numbers (time windows, confidence scores,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     795[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     medication doses, threshold values), and one accidental
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     796[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     float crashes a write.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     797[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     798[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if isinstance(value, float):
