[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Step 8: Track Referral Lifecycles to Closure
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Referrals are first-class coordination objects with a structured lifecycle (ordered, communicated, scheduled, attended, consult-note-received, closed). Each transition has specified time windows. The referral-lifecycle subsystem is a state machine; the LLM operates on top of it.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     def handle_referral_event(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         self,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         *,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    3520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id,
