[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    4396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Run it (`python care_coordination_assistant_demo.py`) and you will see, in order, the enrollment artifact with David's wife designated as caregiver and the cross-organizational consent posture captured; the four ingestion events (FHIR encounter, HL7 discharge, pharmacy fill, referral order) each writing a provenance entry, a coordination-state entry, and the relevant downstream events; the seam-detection rule engine flagging the post-discharge follow-up as needing validation and emitting an engagement scheduling event; the transition-of-care workflow initiated with the post-discharge protocol; the referral lifecycle moved into the `ordered` state and a follow-up scheduling check-in queued; the medication-reconciliation seam raised when the patient-reported 60mg dose conflicts with the discharge 40mg dose (the David scenario); a conversation turn from Margaret asking about the EP referral, going through input safety, identity verification, coordination-context loading, the agent's tool-use loop (with patient_id-cross-check and proxy-scope validation), and the output-safety pipeline; and the weekly digest plus monthly summary plus illustrative outcome-correlation metrics. The audit artifacts at the bottom show the audit surface a real production deployment would feed into Firehose, S3 (with separate KMS for the provenance journal), DynamoDB, EventBridge, and CloudWatch.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    4397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    4398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m What this does not show is the cross-region failover, the IAM least privilege, the per-Lambda VPC posture with PrivateLink to the EHR vendors and HIE, the WAF rule tuning, the load-test data, the per-cohort dashboards, the mandatory-reporting routing variations by state, the production faithfulness verifier with held-out validation, or the complete OpenAPI schemas for the thirteen action-group tools. Each of those is genuine production work that this sketch deliberately leaves to the reader.
