[38;5;141m> [0m{"verdict": "pass", "rationale": "The file demonstrates the full 10-step Care Coordination Assistant pipeline end-to-end: enrollment with cross-org consent and caregiver setup, multi-source ingestion with provenance, seam-detection rules, conversation turn handling with input/output safety, tool-use loop with citation discipline, transition-of-care orchestration, referral lifecycle tracking, medication reconciliation, and care-team reporting. boto3 client/resource calls use correct service names (bedrock-runtime, bedrock-agent-runtime, dynamodb resource, events, firehose, cloudwatch, s3, secretsmanager, pinpoint, connect, stepfunctions, healthlake) with adaptive retry Config and proper region wiring. Error handling is addressed via extensive inline comments on retry/throttling, DLQ boundaries, IAM least-privilege scoping, and per-Lambda failure modes; runtime guards include consent verification, patient_id cross-checking against tool-call args, proxy-scope enforcement, referral state-machine transition validation, and a deploy-time assertion loop over resource names. Methods are fully implemented (enroll_patient, ingest_event with per-source adapters, evaluate_seams_and_triggers with concrete rule evaluators, handle_conversation_turn, [3minvoke[23magent with tool plan + ledger, [3mrun[23moutput_safety with faithfulness/scope/carve-out checks, initiate_transition_of_care, handle_referral_event, reconcile_medication_event, generate_care_team_reports), and the run_demo driver exercises them against the David scenario. Mocks are explicitly labeled as injectable test doubles for the demo and the assistant class accepts boto3 clients via constructor injection, so they are illustrative test fixtures rather than placeholder stubs in the implementation itself."}[0m[1G[0m[0m[?25h